tasks.details:
Create a `.env.local` file and add `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` and `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` variables with values from your Supabase project settings. Install the Supabase client library: `npm install @supabase/supabase-js`. Create a utility file (e.g., `lib/supabase.ts`) to initialize the Supabase client.
```typescript
// lib/supabase.ts
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js'

const supabaseUrl = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
const supabaseAnonKey = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

if (!supabaseUrl || !supabaseAnonKey) {
  throw new Error('Missing Supabase environment variables')
}

export const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseAnonKey)
```

Examine the WowDash template's styling (e.g., in `templates/wowdash/dist/assets/css/style.css` or `html` files) to identify core colors, font sizes, spacing, etc. Add these to the `theme.extend.colors` section of `tailwind.config.js`.
```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  // ...
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        'primary-wow': '#1a73e8', // Example color from WowDash
        'secondary-wow': '#f0f2f5',
        // ... other WowDash colors
      },
      // ... other design tokens like fonts, spacing
    },
  },
  // ...
}
```
